_exptl_absorpt_special_details   
; 
Neutron linear absorption coefficient is wavelength dependent.
For each peak, the absorption coefficient mu is calculated as:
          mu = 0.7700 + 1.1180/1.7982 * wavelength  [cm^-1^]
where 
 0.7700 cm^-1 is the absorption coefficient for total scattering;
 1.1180 cm^-1 is the absorption coefficient for true absorption at 1.7982 A.
 
The value of 0.1392 (mm^-1^) shown in _exptl_absorpt_coefficient_mu 
is the sample absorption coefficient for neutron wavelength at 1.0 \%A.
;

